data.enText: the main ship in a fleet of ships in the navy

data.chText: （某组织机构的）最重要产品，最佳服务项目，主建筑物，王牌
data.enText: the most important product, service, building, etc. that an organization owns or produces

data.chText: 这家公司将在伦敦新开一家旗舰店。
data.enText: The company is opening a new flagship store in London.

word_means: 最重要产品，最佳服务项目，主建筑物，王牌

means: (某组织机构的)最重要产品，最佳服务项目，主建筑物，王牌

tr: the ship that carries the commander of a fleet and flies his flag
the chief one of a related group

value.def: A flagship is the most important ship in a fleet of ships, especially the one on which the commander of the fleet is sailing.
value.tran: 旗舰;(尤指指挥官所在的)主舰

value.def: The flagship of a group of things that are owned or produced by a particular organization is the most important one.

example.ex: The hospital has been the government's flagship, leading the health service reforms...
example.tran: 这家医院一直是政府的旗舰机构，引领着医疗服务的改革。

example.ex: The company plans to open a flagship store in New York this month.
example.tran: 公司计划本月在纽约开一家旗舰店。

value.tran: 王牌;主打产品;旗舰产品
